title: Live: Pies, Blues kick off AFLW season
text:
Top 5 AFLW players to watch 2:53 Live AFLW coverage of Round 1, 2017: Carlton v Collingwood, first game of inaugural AFL Women’s season February 3, 2017 6:03pm by Staff writers Source: FOX SPORTS THE AFLW is here — and it’s kicking off with a traditional blockbuster as Collingwood and Carlton clash at the Blues’ famous home of Ikon Park. 
Over 10,000 fans are expected to flock to the ground, with the AFL not ruling out up to 20,000, after the game was moved from Olympic Park (capacity 5000-7000) to the Blues’ ground (capacity 22,000). 
Both teams are potential premiers according to bookmakers, with the Blues equal-second favourites and the Magpies fourth in the eight-team competition. 
Star forward Moana Hope and captain Steph Chiocci will feature for Collingwood while Carlton fans will be watching for skipper Lauren Arnell and former Matilda Brianna Davey.

The first bounce is at 7:40PM AEDT with live coverage on Fox Footy from 7:30PM. 
The match kicks off a big weekend which sees two games on Saturday — Adelaide Crows v GWS Giants and Western Bulldogs v Fremantle — followed by Sunday’s clash between Melbourne and the Brisbane Lions.
